<bioghist encodinganalog="545"><p><persname>Harvey S. Day</persname> was a dairy farmer of Willis, Michigan and an officer of the Holstein-Friesian Association.</p></bioghist>

<scopecontent><p>Personal and family correspondence, including letter, <date type="single">1865</date>, of <persname>Matthew Day</persname> written from Joe Holt Hospital; letters, 1892-1935, concerning Holstein-Friesian cattle and the activities of the Holstein-Friesian Association, and Day's dairy farm; also bills, receipts, cattle transfer certificates, records of milk poundage, account books, <genreform>poetry</genreform>, <genreform>recipe book</genreform>, and other miscellaneous papers.</p></scopecontent>

